text.section:
The Department may revoke any facility permit issued under this subtitle if the Department finds that:
False or inaccurate information was contained in the application;
Conditions or requirements of the facility permit have been or are about to be violated;
Substantial deviation from plans, specifications, or requirements has occurred;
The Department has been refused entry to the premises for the purpose of inspecting to insure compliance with the conditions of the facility permit;
A change in conditions exists that requires temporary or permanent reduction or elimination of any permitted discharge;
Any State or federal water quality standard or effluent limitation has been or is threatened to be violated; or
Any other good cause exists for revoking the permit.
